FBIS3-27190 "drchi035_h_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 West Europe PRC Officials Meets Italian Senate President Qian Qichen Receives Senate Leader OW1902131694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1238 GMT 19 Feb 94 OW1902131694 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, February 19 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen met with visiting Italian Senate President Giovanni Spatolini here this afternoon. They exchanged views on bilateral relations and international issues of common concern. Qian said that Sino-Italian ties are close, with frequent high- level contacts, adding that spatolini's current China visit would further promote the relations between the two countries. Spatolini recalled his first China tour in 1985 when he was the italian defense minister, noting that great changes have taken place in Beijing since then. Touching on religious issues, Qian said that China has recently promulgated two regulations on religion, pointing out that the purpose of this move "is to protect the normal religious activities instead of limiting them". Earlier today, Spatolini delivered a speech at Beijing University, where he also received an honorary doctorate in history.
